%% RTPI LangGraph Orchestrator State Machine
%% Use: Reference for implementing StateGraph nodes and edges
%% File: docs/diagrams/langgraph-state-machine.mermaid

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> OperatorInput
    OperatorInput --> PlanningAgent: Parse scope & objectives
    
    PlanningAgent --> ReconAgent: mem0.search() for prior context
    
    state ReconFork <<fork>>
    ReconAgent --> ReconFork: Parallel fan-out
    
    ReconFork --> WebDiscovery: Subfinder, Gobuster
    ReconFork --> NetworkScan: Nmap, Masscan
    ReconFork --> OSINTGather: theHarvester, social
    ReconFork --> CloudEnum: ScoutSuite, Prowler
    
    state ReconJoin <<join>>
    WebDiscovery --> ReconJoin
    NetworkScan --> ReconJoin
    OSINTGather --> ReconJoin
    CloudEnum --> ReconJoin
    
    ReconJoin --> mem0Store1: mem0.add(findings, user_id=engagement)
    mem0Store1 --> SkillDiscovery: Query relevant vuln skills
    
    state VulnFork <<fork>>
    SkillDiscovery --> VulnFork: Parallel assessment
    
    VulnFork --> WebVulnAgent: PayloadsATT + API Security plugin
    VulnFork --> InfraVulnAgent: Nuclei + network skills
    VulnFork --> ADVulnAgent: pentest-ad plugin + BloodHound
    VulnFork --> CloudVulnAgent: pentest-cloud plugin
    VulnFork --> CodeReviewAgent: secure-code-review plugin
    
    state VulnJoin <<join>>
    WebVulnAgent --> VulnJoin
    InfraVulnAgent --> VulnJoin
    ADVulnAgent --> VulnJoin
    CloudVulnAgent --> VulnJoin
    CodeReviewAgent --> VulnJoin
    
    VulnJoin --> mem0Store2: mem0.add(vulns, severity metadata)
    mem0Store2 --> SeverityCheck
    
    state SeverityCheck <<choice>>
    SeverityCheck --> HumanApproval: Critical/High vulns found
    SeverityCheck --> ThreatModel: Only Medium/Low/Info
    
    ThreatModel --> ReportingAgent: threat-modeler plugin
    
    HumanApproval --> ExploitAgent: Operator approves
    HumanApproval --> ReportingAgent: Operator declines
    
    ExploitAgent --> BinaryCheck
    
    state BinaryCheck <<choice>>
    BinaryCheck --> RevEngAgent: Custom binary/protocol found
    BinaryCheck --> PostExploitAgent: Standard exploitation
    
    RevEngAgent --> PostExploitAgent: RE findings inform exploit
    
    state PostExFork <<fork>>
    PostExploitAgent --> PostExFork
    
    PostExFork --> PersistenceAgent: C2 persistence
    PostExFork --> PrivEscAgent: Escalation paths
    PostExFork --> LateralMovAgent: Network pivoting
    PostExFork --> DataCollectAgent: Targeted collection
    
    state PostExJoin <<join>>
    PersistenceAgent --> PostExJoin
    PrivEscAgent --> PostExJoin
    LateralMovAgent --> PostExJoin
    DataCollectAgent --> PostExJoin
    
    PostExJoin --> mem0Store3: mem0.add(post-ex, graph relationships)
    mem0Store3 --> ReportingAgent
    
    ReportingAgent --> [*]: pentest-report plugin + mem0 graph
    
    note right of HumanApproval
        CRITICAL: Never auto-exploit
        Operator must confirm scope
        and rules of engagement
    end note
    
    note right of mem0Store2
        Metadata filters:
        severity, domain, technique,
        confidence, status
    end note
    
    note right of RevEngAgent
        Plugins used:
        reverse-binary
        reverse-malware
        reverse-protocol
        reverse-firmware
        reverse-obfuscation
    end note
